<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771051>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. Mandible, inferior tooth. Scale=0.5 mm. A) Triangular, tip clearly angled (A. albata female, BBSL510289). B) Ovular, tip and general form rounded (A. estebana male, BBSL276281). C) Ridge-like, concave above, often projecting off main blade at tip (A. abroniae female, BBSL502235). D) Absent (A. abroniae male, BBSL502217)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771051/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771053>
    dc:description "FIGURE 35. Scutum, impunctate areas. Scale=0.5 mm. A) Absent, evenly pitted or at most negligible (A. estebana female, BBSL842373). B) Present, but relatively small, near cutoff (A. petrophila female, BBSL366021)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771053/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771055>
    dc:description "FIGURE 36. Female T4, unpitted rim medial length. Scale=0.5 mm. A) Short, relatively linear (A. curta, BBSL984034). B) Extended, relatively triangular (A. estebana, BBSL842373). Intermediate forms are given as “moderate.”" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771055/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771059>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Male sterna, S5 setae density and S6 rim form. Scale=0.5 mm. A) S5 with sparse setae; S6 medially emarginate, at least vaguely triangularly, evenly so (A. estebana, 72476). B) S5 setae density high, appearing tufted; S6 medially emarginate, at least vaguely triangularly, but at least slightly filled medially, sometimes tufted (A. maculifrons, 82068). C) S5 with sparse setae; S6 entire or nearly so, with transparent square of integument (A. petrophila, BBSL655748). D) S5 setae density high; S6 entire, medially knobbed (A. flavocincta, BBSL504065)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771059/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771063>
    dc:description "FIGURE 40. Female face of A) Anthophora curta (BBSL502530), B) A. erythrothorax (BBSL502591), C) A. escalante (BBSL1048583), D) A. estebana (BBSL817462), E) A. exigua (BBSL502774), F) A. flavocincta (BBSL504135). Scale=0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771063/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771073>
    dc:description "FIGURE 45. Female habitus of A) Anthophora curta (BBSL502504), B) A. erythrothorax (UCRCENT335467), C) A. escalante (BBSL1048559), D) A. estebana (BBSL502610), E) A. exigua (82036), F) A. flavocincta (BBSL504157). Scale=1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771073/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771085>
    dc:description "FIGURE 50. Male face of A) Anthophora curta (BBSL502451), B) A. erythrothorax (BBSL502589), C) A. escalante (BBSL1026857), D) A. estebana (KWC0014770), E) A. exigua (BBSL502708), F) A. flavocincta (BBSL504072). Scale=0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771085/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771095>
    dc:description "FIGURE 55. Male habitus of A) Anthophora curta (FDP747444), B) A. erythrothorax (UCRCENT335472), C) A. escalante (BBSL1026857), D) A. estebana (BBSL920057), E) A. exigua (82021), F) A. flavocincta (BBSL504079). Scale=1 mm." ;
